   private final Router router;

   @Inject
   NodesBlock(Router router, ViewContext ctx) {
-    super(ctx);
+    super(router, ctx);
     this.router = router;
   }

   @Override
   protected void render(Block html) {
-    // Get the node info from the federation
+
+    boolean isEnabled = isYarnFederationEnabled();
+
+    // If Yarn Federation is not enabled, the user needs to be prompted.
+    initUserHelpInformationDiv(html, isEnabled);

Review Comment:
   I'm not sure we should show the not enabled always.
   Most users won't care about federation and they would see this error.

